ated_timestamp\":\"0\",\"copyright\":\"\",\"focal_length\":\"0\",\"iso\":\"0\",\"shutter_speed\":\"0\",\"title\":\"Lorna family .jpg\",\"orientation\":\"0\"}\" data-image-title=\"AD_235944714.jpg\" data-image-description=\"<p>Lorna family .jpg</p> \" data-medium-file=\"https://metrouk2.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/ad_235944714.jpg?quality=80&strip=all&w=274&strip=all\" data-large-file=\"https://metrouk2.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/ad_235944714.jpg?quality=80&strip=all&w=937&strip=all\" class=\"img-align-none size-full wp-image-6464764\" src=\"https://metrouk2.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/ad_235944714.jpg?quality=80&strip=all&strip=all\" alt=\"Lorna family .jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"1120\" /></div><figcaption>Pretty good (Picture: Facebook)</figcaption></figure> For some, feeding your family for around 62p a portion sounds like the dream.\nBut Lorna Cooper has managed to cut down the overall weekly food cost by buying everything in bulk ahead of time.\nThen, to prevent food waste, she freezes any leftovers they have.\n<a href=\"http://metro.co.uk/2017/02/22/tube-and-rail-strikes-continue-to-cause-commuter-choas-6464701\" data-track=\"zone-post-thumbnail-link\" data-track-destination=\"6464701\" class=\"thumbnail-link\"><img src=\"http://i0.wp.com/metrouk2.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/ad235716819file-photo-dated.jpg?crop=390px%2C0px%2C2727px%2C2044px&resize=150%2C113&quality=80&strip=all&ssl=1&w=100&h=75\" data-aspect=\"1.3274336283186\" class=\"thumbnail-link-image\" data-rewritten=\"false\" /><span class=\"mor-title\">Tube and rail strikes continue to cause commuter choas</span></a> She claims that, as a result, her food budget is only around ÂŁ16.60 a week for her family of four.\nLorna apparently gets a ÂŁ65 box from Muscle Food, an online food shop, which lasts her family for around six weeks.\nWhile the box is only made up of meat, she also orders vegetables and cupboard staples from the site.\n<figure class=\"aligncenter img-container shareable-item\" style=\"max-width:620px\"><div class=\"img-wrap\"><a id=\"item-attachment_6464757\" class=\"anchor\"></a><div class=\"item-share-buttons item-share\"><a class=\"share-item share-item-facebook btn\" title=\"Share this on Facebook\" data-track=\"share-item-facebook\"><span class=\"icon icon-facebook\"></span></a><a class=\"share-item share-item-twitter btn\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Share this on Twitter\" data-track=\"share-item-twitter\"><span class=\"icon icon-twitter\"></span></a><a class=\"share-item share-item-pinterest btn\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Share this on Pinterest\" data-track=\"share-item-pinterest\"><span class=\"icon icon-pinterest\"></span></a></div><img data-attachment-id=\"6464757\" data-permalink=\"http://metro.co.uk/?attachment_id=6464757\" data-orig-file=\"https://metrouk2.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/mg_moneysaving_food_comp.jpg?quality=80&strip=all&strip=all\" data-orig-size=\"1200,625\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{\"aperture\":\"0\",\"credit\":\"\",\"camera\":\"\",\"caption\":\"\",\"created_timestamp\":\"0\",\"copyright\":\"\",\"focal_length\":\"0\",\"iso\":\"0\",\"shutter_speed\":\"0\",\"title\":\"\",\"orientation\":\"1\"}\" data-image-title=\"mg_moneysaving_food_comp\" data-image-description=\"<p>Supersaver mum feeds a family of five for just ÂŁ16.60 a WEEK â€“ and hereâ€™s how you can make delicious meals for just 62p a portion</p> <p>Facebook</p> \" data-medium-file=\"https://metrouk2.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/mg_moneysaving_food_comp.jpg?quality=80&strip=all&w=300&strip=all\" data-large-file=\"https://metrouk2.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/mg_moneysaving_food_comp.jpg?quality=80&strip=all&w=1024&strip=all\" class=\"img-align-none size-full wp-image-6464757\" src=\"https://metrouk2.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/mg_moneysaving_food_comp.jpg?quality=80&strip=all&strip=all\" alt=\"Impressive (Picture: Facebook)\" width=\"1024\" height=\"533\" /></div><figcaption>Impressive (Picture: Facebook)</figcaption></figure> To save even more money, however, you could get a fresh veg hamper for ÂŁ10 a week for four people – which works out around ÂŁ5 cheaper every six weeks than if you buy the meat one. You could then supplement your order with grains and spices.\n<a href=\"http://metro.co.uk/2017/02/22/brace-yourselves-storm-doris-is-going-to-hit-with-blizzards-with-80mph-winds-6464590\" data-track=\"zone-post-thumbnail-link\" data-track-destination=\"6464590\" class=\"thumbnail-link\"><img src=\"http://i1.wp.com/metrouk2.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/doris2.jpg?crop=180px%2C0px%2C842px%2C630px&resize=150%2C113&quality=80&strip=all&ssl=1&w=100&h=75\" data-aspect=\"1.3274336283186\" class=\"thumbnail-link-image\" data-rewritten=\"false\" /><span class=\"mor-title\">Brace yourselves! Storm Doris is going to hit with blizzards with 80mph winds</span></a> Lorna, from Blocharin in Glasgow, said: ‘I’ve always watched what I’ve spent when it comes to the grocery bill, and over the years have learnt a lot of different ways to make meals stretch further.\n‘I’ve definitely learnt that bulk-ordering wholesome and healthy ingredients instead of regular trips to the shop is a great way to prep ahead and make food last.’\nShe also runs a Facebook page called ‘<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/fyf20quid\" target=\"_blank\">Feed your family for about ÂŁ20 a week</a>‘, or ‘FYF’ for short, on which she gives regular money-saving advice and recipes.", "external_links": [], "published": "2017-02-22T16:19:00.000+02:00", "crawled": "2017-02-22T12:08:17.979+02:00", "highlightTitle": ""}